      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 150: The background transition deactivates every DHT-proxy-enabled account without checking whether the account was already deliberately disabled by the user. `setAccountsActiveForBackground(true)` later reactivates all proxy-enabled accounts, so an account that was disabled before the app went to background can be unintentionally brought online after foreground return or a push. Preserve each account\u0027s prior daemon/user activation state before background deactivation and restore only those that were active. For example, track the account ids deactivated by this feature and only reactivate that set:\n```suggestion\n// before deactivation, record only proxy accounts that are currently active\nmAccountService.deactivateProxyAccountsForBackground()\n\n// on foreground/push, restore only accounts deactivated by this path\nmAccountService.restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground()\n```",
      "revId": "8beea6951b74251b4a9846ff5268527bcb783099",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
