      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 94: `isDhtProxyCallWakeup` treats a missing `pt` field plus high original priority as a call push. The comment notes message-channel requests may also be high priority, so minimal non-call high-priority payloads will get the longer call grace window and keep accounts active for up to 60s unnecessarily. Prefer a positive call signal only, or fall back to high priority only when the payload is known to be from the DHT proxy call wakeup format.\n```suggestion\nreturn pushType?.let { it \u003d\u003d \"audioCall\" || it \u003d\u003d \"videoCall\" } \u003d\u003d true\n```",
      "revId": "8beea6951b74251b4a9846ff5268527bcb783099",
